modules.description: This module provides migration annotations that facilitate converting code from using the Stdlib to Base. It includes type definitions and value mappings that align Stdlib types and functions with their Base equivalents. Use this module when transitioning existing OCaml projects from the standard library to Base to maintain compatibility during the migration process.

This module provides attributes to migrate code from older Stdlib names to their modern equivalents, such as replacing `acos` with `Float.acos`. It operates on OCaml source code through attributes that guide the renaming process during compilation. Use it to update codebases to align with current Stdlib naming conventions without runtime impact.
